Anonymous Sun 30 May 2021 20:16:15 No.39058272 Report
Quoted By: >>39058400 >>39058540
>>39058118
>Dolphins, cephalopods, elephants which are pretty close to human intelligence.
None of them have been proven to have an intellect close to ours, they merely display some signs of it. Once again this banks on a disproven theory that memory equals intelligence, which it doesn't. There's yet to be an animal that displays true sentience, beyond that of simple self-awareness which many animals possess. The largest key difference being the lack of judgement in animals, and the absence of morality in their actions. Animals cannot think in abstract.

Animals may present /indications/ of sapience, such as social groups and the usage of tools, but no true sapience. Even the most 'intelligent' of animals do not possess capabilities above that of a toddler's in terms of thought.
